<h1><a href="nest-apple-store">Nest at the online Apple Store?</a></h1>

<p><img src="http://dl.dropbox.com/u/1276566/umtitled/post_images/nest.jpg" alt="Nest"></p>

<p>This is baffling to me: </p>

<blockquote>
  <p><a href="http://www.nest.com/">Nest</a>, the learning thermostat created by [former Apple employee] Tony Fadell has been added to Apple's online store as of this morning.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Okay, I get the connections; it's very Apple-ish in its UI, it's got apps, and it's... umm... okay, that's all I got. It's just a weird fit for the (online) Apple Store. Most, if not all, of the third party stuff Apple sells exists to enhance their products. So apps are sold to enhance the iPhone, laptop bags enhance laptops, etc... But that paradigm is backwards with the Nest. In this scenario, the iPhone is the third party enhancement to the Nest. Now that's not very Apple-ish.</p>

<p>I'm reluctant to say it, but this never would have happened under the  Jobs regime.</p>

<p><a href="http://www.redmondpie.com/nest-learning-thermostat-now-available-at-apple-stores/">Nest Learning Thermostat Now Available At Apple Stores &rarr;</a></p>

